1. Bring 2 cups water to a boil in a 3-quart heavy saucepan.
Stir in 1 cup of rice.
2. Cover. Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes or until all the water is absorbed. Fluff lightly with fork and serve.
Cooking directions in the microwave:
1. In a 2-quart microwave-safe dish combine 2 cups of water and 1 cup of rice*.
2. Cover. Microwave on high for 5 minutes.
3. Reduce setting to 50% power, microwave for 15 minutes or until all the water is absorbed.
4. Fluff lightly with fork and serve.
*Add 1 tbsp. tub margarine and 1 tsp. salt per cup of uncooked rice, if desired.
For drier rice use 1 3/4 cups water. For moister rice, use 2 1/4 cups water.</directions><grocery><ingredients>Long Grain Rice, Iron Phosphate, Niacin, Thiamine Mononitrate, and Folic Acid.</ingredients><kosherCodes><kosherCode>1</kosherCode></kosherCodes><nutritions><nutrition sequence="1"><numberOfServings>20</numberOfServings><servingSizes><servingSize type="us"><measure>0.25</measure><uom>c</uom></servingSize></servingSizes><energy>160</energy><totalFat uom="g" dailyPct="0" calories="0">0</totalFat><saturatedFat uom="g" dailyPct="0" calories="">0</saturatedFat><transFat uom="g">0</transFat><cholesterol uom="mg" dailyPct="0">0</cholesterol><sodium uom="mg" dailyPct="0">0</sodium><carbohydrates uom="g" dailyPct="12">35</carbohydrates><dietaryFiber uom="g">0</dietaryFiber><sugars uom="g">0</sugars><protein uom="g" dailyPct="">3</protein><dailyPercentOfVitaminA>0</dailyPercentOfVitaminA><dailyPercentOfVitaminC>0</dailyPercentOfVitaminC><dailyPercentOfCalcium>0</dailyPercentOfCalcium><dailyPercentOfIron>8</dailyPercentOfIron><dailyPercentOfFolicAcid>15</dailyPercentOfFolicAcid><dailyPercentOfNiacin>8</dailyPercentOfNiacin><dailyPercentOfThiamin>15</dailyPercentOfThiamin></nutrition></nutritions></grocery></product></products><attributes/></item><item id="00045440-4148-11e1-8ec7-005056957023" status="P"><name>Caress Velvet Bliss Ultra Silkening Beauty Bar - 6 CT</name><marketingDescription>Caress?? 2 cups boiling water.
1/2 cup milk.
1 tablespoon margarine or butter.
Oven directions:
1. Heat oven to 450 degrees F. Stir 1 packet sauce mix, boiling water, milk and margarine with whisk in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Stir in 1 pouch potatoes.
2. Bake uncovered about 25 minutes or until top is golden brown and potatoes are tender (sauce will thicken as it stands). Stir before serving. Refrigerate leftovers.
Baking tips:
For entire box, double all ingredients; bake in 3-quart casserole dish about 30 minutes.
Bake potatoes and roast meat at same time: 325 degrees F about 60 minutes; 350 degrees F about 50 minutes; 
375 degrees F about 45 minutes.
Stove top directions:
For 4 1/2 servings (half box).
1. Stir 1 packet sauce mix, 2 cups hot water, 1/2 cup milk, 1 tablespoon margarine or butter and 1 pouch potatoes in 2-quart saucepan. Heat to boiling, stirring frequently.
Watch carefully to avoid boilover.
2. Reduce heat to medium; gently boil uncovered 8 minutes, stirring frequently. Reduce heat; cover and simmer about 7 minutes, stirring frequently, until tender (sauce will thicken as it stands). Refrigerate leftovers.
Microwave directions:
For 4 1/2 servings (half box).
1. Stir 1 packet sauce mix, 2 1/2 cups hot water, 1/2 cup milk, 1 tablespoon margarine or butter and 1 pouch potatoes in 3-quart round microwavable casserole dish.
2. Microwave uncovered on high 15 to 20 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes, until tender (sauce will thicken as it stands).
Caution: dish will be hot. Refrigerate leftovers.</directions><grocery><ingredients>Potatoes*, Enriched Flour (Wheat Flour, Niacin, Iron, Thiamin Mononitrate, Riboflavin, Folic Acid), Maltodextrin, Corn Starch, Sea Salt, Potassium Phosphate. If you do not know if your prescription drug contains an MAOI, ask a doctor or pharmacist before taking this product.&#xD;
Ask a doctor before use if you have:&#xD;
A cough that occurs with too much phlegm (mucus).&#xD;
A cough that lasts or is chronic such as occurs with smoking, asthma, or emphysema.&#xD;
Stop use and ask a doctor or dentist if:&#xD;
Cough lasts for more than 7 days, comes back, or is accompanied by fever, rash, or persistent headache. These could be signs of a serious condition.&#xD;
Sore mouth symptoms do not improve in 7 days.&#xD;
If pregnant or breast-feeding, ask a health professional before use.&#xD;
Keep out of reach of children. In case of overdose, get medical help or contact a Poison Control Center right away.&#xD;
Should be 18 or older to purchase.</warning></warnings><directions>Do not take more than 12 lozenges in any 24-hour period.&#xD;
This adult product is not intended for use in children under 12 years of age.&#xD;
Allow lozenges (one immediately after the other) to dissolve slowly in the mouth.&#xD;
Age: Adults and children 12 years of age and over - Dose: 2 lozenges every 4 hours.&#xD;
Age: Children under 12 years - Dose: do not use.&#xD;
Other information:&#xD;
Store at 20-25 degrees C (68-77 degrees F). Store in a dry place.</directions><grocery><ingredients>Active Ingredients (in Each Lozenge) - Purposes.

P.F. Chang's® expert chefs highly recommend following stove top directions.

Stove top:

0g trans fat per serving.
Naturally cholesterol free.
No artificial preservatives.
No artificial colors or flavors.
Naturally you care, and so do we...
Why is it that better for you, better for the environment products are often worse for your wallet? Every family deserves to have healthier, affordable, all natural products - and now they can! Mom's Best Naturals cereals provide a way to help care for your family's health, your wallet and the environment.
It's likely we've all experienced the frustration of purchasing one of those expensive cereals that your family just won't eat and consequently, ends up in the trash. With Mom's Best Naturals, you are guaranteed delicious cereal made with wholesome, all natural ingredients.
No artificial colors, flavors or preservatives, no hydrogenated this or high-fructose that.
Yes, we do add natural sugar to ensure a delightful tasting cereal that your family is sure to love, but combined with fresh fruit and healthy dairy, Mom's Best Naturals becomes part of a well balanced meal and a great start to the day!
What your family eats matters to you, but so does the impact your family has on mother earth. Like you, our commitment goes beyond the natural goodness of cereal.
We continually strive to make choices that promote sustainability.
Our cereals are made with renewable wind energy, and our diligent recycling and water reduction efforts help to conserve natural resources. Even this box you're reading is printed with vegetable-based inks on recycled paperboard!
We all know that little things can make a big difference and this idea has mattered to us since 1919. Mom's Best Naturals cereals are a delicious, affordable and environmentally friendly way to do what's right for the people around your breakfast table and around the planet.
You'll taste it in every bite!
Since 2006, we've purchased more than 10 million kilowatt hours of renewable wind energy, a benefit equal to taking nearly 1,350 cars off the road!
More than 95% of waste materials were recycled at our Minnesota and North Carolina plants. This diverted thousands of tons of materials from local landfills.
Calculated for the following waste materials generated in 2010: packaging, dry ingredients, partially processed cereal, cereal dust, and ordinary trash.
Between 2008-2010, our Utah plant reduced water usage equivalent to conserving more than 22 million gallons! That equals 52 football fields covered with a foot of water!
To continue the conversation about healthier, affordable, all natural products, go to: momsbestnaturals.com.
*We purchase wind energy credits to offset 100% of the electricity used to make the cereal in this box.

1. Spray in cold oven. If you have a self-cleaning oven, make sure self-cleaning cycle is turned off and oven is cold. Hold can upright, pointed away from face. 1. Spray in cold oven. Hold can upright, pointed away from face. Liberally spray spots from a distance of 9-12 inches by pointing arrow on spray button to dot.
2. Allow to stand for 30 sec. -1 min.
3. Wipe clean with a wet sponge, cloth or paper towels.

Do not use if you have never had a vaginal yeast infection diagnosed by a doctor.
Ask a doctor before use if you have:
Vaginal itching and discomfort for the first time.
Lower abdominal, back or shoulder pain, fever, chills, nausea, vomiting, or foul-smelling vaginal discharge. You may have a more serious condition.
Vaginal yeast infections often (such as once a month or 3 in 6 months). You could be pregnant or have a serious underlying medical cause for your symptoms, including diabetes or a weakened immune system.
Been exposed to human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) that causes aids.
When using this product:
Do not use tampons, douches, spermicides, or other vaginal products. Condoms and diaphragms may be damaged and fail to prevent pregnancy or sexually transmitted disease (STDs).
Do not have vaginal intercourse.
Mild increase in vaginal burning, itching or irritation may occur.
If you do not get complete relief, ask a doctor before using another product.
Stop use and ask a doctor if:
Symptoms do not get better after 3 days.
Symptoms last more than 7 days.
You get a rash or hives, abdominal pain, fever, chills, nausea, vomiting, or foul-smelling vaginal discharge.
If pregnant or breast-feeding, ask a health professional before use.

"The greatest cookies in the world!"
D.W. was busy making cookies with her mom. "Arthur is going to love these sugar cookies" said D.W., "They are better than any cookies in the whole world!"
"First, let's get them into the oven so they have time to cool before dinner" said D.W.'s mom. D.W. danced around the kitchen singing, "Yum, yum, yum. My cookies are the best cookies ever!" Finally the timer went off and the cookies were ready.
Arthur and his dad walked into the kitchen. "Something smells so good!" said Arthur, "What is it?" "I made sugar cookies for dessert," said D.W., "and they are the best cookies in the whole world!" "Let me test one," said Dad. "Me too!" said Arthur popping two cookies into his mouth. "Hey, don't eat them all. There won't be any left for dessert!" said D.W. quickly grabbing a cookie. "Don't worry D.W.," said Mom. "We have plenty of cookie mixes here in the cupboard. We'll make some more and you bring them to school tomorrow. They're safe for everyone to eat!"
"These really are the best sugar cookies in the world," said Arthur. He reached for another cookie. Dad reached for another too. Mom and D.W. did too. Everyone laughed as they finished their cookies.
"I told you my cookies are the best cookies in the whole world!" said D.W. And no one disagreed.

Absorbency: Super - Absorbency range: 9-12g.
Absorbency: Super plus - Absorbency range: 12-15g.
Absorbency: Ultra - Absorbency range: 15-18g.

Optimum pan.

Pamela's chocolate cake:
1 bag Pamela's mix.
1/2 cup oil.
Yield: 1 cake.
2 eggs, large.
1-1/2 cup water.
Baking directions: preheat oven to 350 degrees. Whisk together eggs, oil, and water well, then add dry mix and stir to combine. Do not over mix. (Add a 3rd egg for a lighter cake. For denser cake, use 1-1/4 cups water.) Pour batter into lightly greased baking pan. Use pans and bake times listed below. Remove cake when toothpick comes out almost clean.
When cool, frost with Pamela's vanilla or dark chocolate frosting, whipped cream, your favorite frosting, powdered sugar, cover with berries, or use nothing at all!

Adult dog feeding instructions: The recommended feeding amounts indicated are based upon the average nutritional needs of an adult dog with a normal activity level (using a standard 8 oz/250 ml measuring cup, which contains approximately 92 g of Purina One). Factors, such as a dog's metabolism, breed size, activity level, age and whether the dog is spayed or neutered, will affect the amount of Purina One needed to maintain an ideal body condition. The pet experts at Purina have provided the feeding amounts indicated as a starting point. If you find that your dog is losing weight or becomes overweight when fed these amounts, please adjust accordingly. To help your dog maintain an ideal body condition, monitor your dog's weight on a regular basis, making sure that his ribs are easily felt and the waist is visible when viewed from above. Maintaining an ideal body condition can impact your dog's lifelong health.&#xD;
It's not for all dogs: Purina One true instinct formula is specifically formulated for adult dogs. If you have a puppy, or a pregnant or nursing dog, feed Purina One SmartBlend healthy puppy formula.&#xD;
May be served dry or moistened: Purina One may be fed dry or mixed with water. If mixed, we suggest one part liquid to four parts Purina One.&#xD;
Making the switch to Purina One: although you'll be anxious to see the difference Purina One can make in your dog, please allow 7-10 days to ease the transition from your dog's current food. Each day, simply feed a little less of the previous food and a little more Purina One until you're feeding Purina One exclusively. This gradual transition will help avoid dietary upsets.&#xD;
No supplements necessary: Purina One provides 100% complete and balanced nutrition for adult dogs. There is no need to add vitamins, minerals or other supplements, unless specifically directed by a veterinarian.&#xD;
Fresh water, proper diet &amp; veterinary care: be sure to provide fresh water in a clean container for your dog daily. Proper diet, exercise and veterinary care are the best ways to keep your dog healthy. If your dog hasn't had a check-up in the past year, please make an appointment today.&#xD;

2 lbs. beef, chicken, pork, or shrimp.

Cook thoroughly.
How to get things cookin':
For food safety and best quality, follow these cooking instructions:
Keep frozen until your'e ready to eat.
Cook thoroughly before eating.
Follow cooking instructions to make sure your product has reached 165 degrees F, as measured by a food thermometer.
Adjustment to cooking time may be required due to variations in all ovens.
Careful because product will be hot!
Conventional oven (from frozen):
Preheat your oven to a toasty 450 degrees F.
Put frozen jalapenos in a single layer on a non-stick baking sheet. Do not stack the peppers!
Let the jalapenos bake for 6 minutes.
Flip them over and bake for another 5 minutes. Watch closely as over heating may cause loss of filling.
Allow jalapenos to rest for a couple minutes before digging in!
Deep fryer (from frozen):
Caution: ice crystals on frozen foods can cause spattering when added to hot oil. Tips for frying with oil: always preheat oil uncovered. If oil spatters, cover immediately and reduce heat. When spattering stops, remove cover and return to cooking temperature. Be careful not to spatter or spill oil onto hot burner of range. Add product carefully.
Preheat oil to 350 degrees F.
Put frozen jalapenos in fryer basket.
Fry frozen jalapenos for 2:15 minutes.
Open fryer and shake basket to evenly distribute.
Close fryer and fry jalapenos for 2 more minutes. Watch closely as over heating may cause loss of filling.
Allow jalapenos to rest for a couple minutes before digging in!</directions><grocery><ingredients>Jalapeno Peppers (Contains Salt, Calcium Chloride), Cream Cheese (Pasteurized Milk and Cream, Cheese Culture, Salt, Carob Bean Gum), Wheat Flour, Soybean Oil, Water, Modified Corn Starch, Palm Oil, Dextrose, Salt, Apocarotenal (Color), Mono and Diglycerides, Ammonium Chloride, Calcium Sulfate, Yeast, Sodium Bicarbonate, Vinegar, Spice Extractive, Egg Whites, Leavening (Sodium Acid Pyrophosphate, Sodium Bicarbonate, Monocalcium Phosphate), Extractive Of Paprika (Color), Dried Garlic, Dried Onion, Nonfat Dry Milk, Sodium Alginate, Spices.</ingredients><foodRelatedIndicators><temperatureIndicator>Frozen</temperatureIndicator></foodRelatedIndicators><nutritions><nutrition sequence="1"><numberOfServings>3</numberOfServings><servingSizes><servingSize type="metric"><measure>77.0</measure><uom>g</uom></servingSize><servingSize type="other"><measure>3.0</measure><uom>pieces</uom></servingSize></servingSizes><energy>230</energy><totalFat uom="g" dailyPct="18" calories="110">12</totalFat><saturatedFat uom="g" dailyPct="25" calories="">5</saturatedFat><transFat uom="g">0</transFat><cholesterol uom="mg" dailyPct="5">15</cholesterol><sodium uom="mg" dailyPct="18">420</sodium><carbohydrates uom="g" dailyPct="6">19</carbohydrates><dietaryFiber uom="g">1</dietaryFiber><sugars uom="g">1</sugars><protein uom="g" dailyPct="">4</protein><dailyPercentOfVitaminA>6</dailyPercentOfVitaminA><dailyPercentOfVitaminC>0</dailyPercentOfVitaminC><dailyPercentOfCalcium>4</dailyPercentOfCalcium><dailyPercentOfIron>0</dailyPercentOfIron></nutrition></nutritions></grocery></product></products><packageDistributor><name>Heinz North America, Division of H.J. See back panel.
Keep out of reach of children.
Warning: eye and skin irritant. Bonds skin instantly.
Contains ethyl cyanoacrylate. Avoid contact with skin and eyes. If eye or mouth contact occurs, hold eyelid or mouth open and rinse thoroughly but gently with water only for 15 minutes and get medical attention. Liquid glue will sting eye temporarily. Solidified glue may irritate eye like a grain of sand and should be treated by an eye doctor. If skin bonding occurs, soak in acetone-based nail polish remover or warm soapy water and carefully peel or roll skin apart (do not pull). Contact through clothing may cause skin burn. If spilled on clothing, flush with cold water. Avoid prolonged breathing of vapors. Use with adequate ventilation. Keep out of reach of children. For emergency medical information only, call toll-free 1-888-516-2502.</warning></warnings><directions>Read instructions before using.
1. Protect work area. Glue may damage fabrics and furniture finishes.
2. Remove glue tube from case. Hold upright and point away from eyes and body. Screw nozzle onto tube. Nozzle automatically pierces tube.
3. Gently squeeze tube applying one to four drops per square inch depending on porosity. Too much glue or spreading glue will make a poor bond or no bond.
4. Parts to be glued should be clean and dry. Parts must mate. Metals may have to be cleaned with a solvent or scraped. Dampen porous ceramics on one side and apply glue to dry side. Sand or plane wood surfaces flat. Remove paint, glue, etc. From surfaces to be bonded.
5. Join the parts and press for 30 seconds. Allow to set for a few minutes.
6. Discard tube when finished.
Not for use on paper, foam, rear view mirrors, polyethylene or fluorinated resin. Do not put bonded items in oven or on stove. Do not use to attach artificial nails. Store in cool, dark place.</directions><grocery/></product></products><packageDistributor><name>Elmer's &amp; Toagosei Co</name><address>460 Polaris Parkway Westerville, OH 43082</address><email/><phone>1-888-435-6377</phone><url>www.krazyglue.com</url></packageDistributor><attributes/></item><item id="00a94570-744e-11e1-a5ca-005056ab0051" status="P"><name>Pepperidge Farm Puff Pastry Turnovers Apple - 4 CT</name><marketingDescription>Pepperidge Farm® Puff Pastry Apple Turnovers.

Instructions:
Bake time may vary depending on oven.
1. Preheat oven to 475 degrees F.
Important: oven must be preheated.
2. Remove desired number of turnovers from packaging. Wrap any remaining frozen turnovers in plastic wrap or foil and return to freezer.
3. Place frozen turnovers 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
4. Immediately reduce oven to 400 degrees F. Place baking sheet in center of the oven.
5. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown and puffed.
6. Remove from baking sheet. Cool on wire rack for 15 minutes, since filling will be very hot. Serve warm.
Helpful hints:
Turnovers may be baked earlier in the day and reheated before serving. Place in preheated 250 degrees F. Oven for 8 minutes to restore crispness. Dark baking sheets, parchment paper, non-stick baking liners and insulated pans may affect the baking time. Adjust time accordingly.

Cinn-fully a la mode: top warm turnover with a scoop of vanilla ice cream, prepared caramel sauce and toasted chopped pecans; sprinkle with ground cinnamon.

Processed in a facility that also uses wheat, milk, eggs, soy, peanuts and tree nuts.</warning></warnings><directions>It's so delicious! How can I make it last longer?&#xD;
Our loyalty to traditional artisan baking, a fundamental age-old bread-making tradition by hand with special attention to ingredients and baking in stone deck ovens, means our breads are as pure as possible. You won't find chemicals, anti-molding agents and preservatives often found in frozen or mass-produced breads. That's why it's best to enjoy Nature's Promise products within a day or two of your purchase. Maximize your enjoyment with these handy tips:&#xD;
Place bread in a plastic bag (i.e., Ziploc) or enclose it with plastic wrap and leave it at room temperature.&#xD;
Never refrigerate the bread - it will stale faster.&#xD;
Our bakers recommend "refreshing" the crust by removing the bread from the plastic and placing the bread in a hot oven - 350 degrees F - for three to five minutes. The crust will regain its crispiness and flavor and the crumb will have a softer texture. This refreshing process works well with any bread that might have "lost" its crust due to humid weather or environmental conditions.&#xD;

MyPyramid.gov.
USDA does not endorse any products, services, or organizations.
Bran Flakes are a delicious way to boost your daily intake of whole grain and fiber.
Bran Flakes with dietary fiber to help maintain digestive Health.
Why is good digestive health important?
Our digestive system has the important job of processing the foods we eat into nutrients needed by our body.
What is the benefit of getting enough Dietary Fiber?
Getting enough fiber in your diet has many benefits and is important for maintaining digestive health. Unfortunately more than 9 out of 10 Americans don&amp;#39;t get the recommended amount of fiber. At least 25g of fiber is recommended daily for most adults.
A smart step towards helping naturally regulate your digestive system is to gradually increase your fiber intake by choosing fiber containing cereals. Choose a diet that is rich in a variety of fiber containing foods such as cereals, whole grains, fruits, vegetables, and legumes. Remember drinking adequate fluids and regular physical activity are also important for digestive health.
How can Post Bran Flakes help maintain your Digestive Health?
Post Bran Flakes can help give your fiber intake a boost! You can get 20% of your Daily Value* for fiber by enjoying a bowl of Post Bran Flakes for Breakfast or as a healthy snack.
It is wise to increase your fiber intake gradually so your digestive system has time to adjust. Suddenly consuming very high amounts of fiber is not recommended because it can cause digestive discomfort. Remember to drink adequate fluids too.
*Percent Daily Values are based on a 2,000 calorie diet.
Your daily values may be higher or lower depending on your calorie needs.
Nutritionists recommend at least 3 servings of whole grain foods each day (about 16g per serving or 48g per day).

Baking instructions:
Recommended pan size: 8 1/2" x 4 1/2" x 2 1/2".
Natural method:
Following these simple steps will allow you to set out your frozen bread dough and forget about it until it has properly risen and is ready to pop into the oven.
1. Thoroughly grease pan with non-stick cooking spray.
2. Place bread dough in pan. Cover with plastic wrap. Plastic wrap must be sprayed with non-stick cooking spray to prevent sticking. Let rise at room temperature (the warmer the better) until one-inch above pan, approximately six hours or more depending on temperature (approximately three hours if using the easy overnight method).
3. Bake at 350 degrees F for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown. Bread is done when it pulls away from sides of pan and sounds hollow when tapped lightly.
4. Remove from pan at once and place on wire rack for cooling. Brush with melted butter or margarine.
5. Place hot bread on side for slicing.
Easy overnight method:
Thawing dough in the refrigerator overnight (or during the day while you are at work) will reduce the time necessary to let the dough rise before baking.
1. Thaw dough in refrigerator (in original bag or plastic wrap) for eight hours. Thawed dough may be kept in refrigerator for up to 24 hours.
2. Proceed with steps 1 through 5 of natural method.
Speed method.
This method will reduce total preparation time by up to 2 hours compared to the "natural method".
1. Place bread dough in a greased pan and cover with plastic wrap that has been sprayed with non-stick cooking spray.
2. Preheat oven to 175 degrees F, then turn oven off!
3. Place bread dough in oven.
4. Let dough rise until one-inch above pan (about 2 to 4 hours). Watch closely to be sure it does not rise too high. Then carefully remove plastic wrap.
5. Leave dough in the oven and set to 350 degrees F. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
6. Proceed with steps 4 and 5 of natural method.
Helpful hints:
1. For the most attractive loaf, use 8 1/2" x 4 1/2" x 2 1/2" metal pan (top inside measurements).
2. Prior to first use, new metal pans should be baked empty at 375 degrees F for one hour.
3. For easiest slicing, let bread cool thoroughly. Place bread on side and slice with a serrated edge knife or electric knife.
4. Should the dough rise too much, simply remove it from the pan, punch it down to its original size and reshape. Then let it rise again to one-inch above the pan, before baking.
5. When storing frozen dough in your freezer, seal tightly in original bag.
6. For best results use within two weeks from date of purchase.
Keep dough frozen.
Use by date on plastic closure tab.</directions><grocery><ingredients>Unbleached Enriched White Flour (Wheat Flour, Niacin, Reduced Iron, Thiamin Mononitrate, Riboflavin, Folic Acid), Water, High For over 50 years, Back To Nature has passionately created foods with wholesome grains, real nutrition, and the delicious flavors of nature free from artificial ingredients. We give people truly flavorful, wholesome foods made with simple ingredients.&#xD;
Here's the great stuff about oat medley oat flakes with cinnamon chia &amp; flax clusters:&#xD;
Taste the goodness of oats and ancient grains when you crunch into this crispy medley. Enjoy flakes made from whole grain rolled oats, whole grain sorghum, and whole grain brown rice blended with sweet cinnamon oat clusters with chia and flax seeds. These wholesome ingredients are simply the best way to kick start your day!&#xD;
Why chia &amp; flax?&#xD;
Chia seeds:&#xD;
Chia seeds have long been touted for their energy-boosting power. The mild-flavored seeds also have more than two times the protein of any other seed or grain. They also contain omega-3 fatty acids, carbohydrates, fiber, antioxidants, and calcium.&#xD;
Flax seeds:&#xD;
Widely considered one of the most powerful plant foods on the planet, flax seeds contain ALA omega-3 essential fatty acids, fiber, and antioxidants.&#xD;
Diets low in saturated fat and cholesterol that include 3 grams of soluble fiber from oats per day may reduce the risk of heart disease. One serving of oat medley contains 1g of this soluble fiber.&#xD;

Certified organic:
Unlike "natural" label claims, certified organic products are guaranteed to have been grown without chemical herbicides and pesticides, and there are never synthetic preservatives or additives. Because, really, who wants any of that for breakfast?
Non-GMO:
"GMO" stands for "Genetically Modified Organisms". Doesn't sound too tasty, does it? The Non-GMO Project agrees, and their verification assures you that the food you're buying is made in a kitchen - not in a lab.
Heart healthy:
Diets low in saturated fat and cholesterol and rich in fruits, vegetables and grain products that contain some types of dietary fiber, particularly soluble fiber, may reduce the risk of heart disease, a disease associated with many factors.

Busy office workers in bustling Mumbai take their lunch from a metal container known as a "tiffin". This is delivered daily by paid "tiffin wallahs" who charge a monthly fee for the service. In this way, thousands of individual fresh lunches move from suburban home to urban office, just in time for lunch.
A staple of many of these meals is a spiced lentil stew known as "dal". Dal makhani is a creamy lentil curry made by simmering black lentils in garlic, ginger and "garam masala" spice blend.
Discover the Taste of India™.

1. Remove the tray from this cardboard carton.

©Bausch &amp; Lomb Incorporated.</otherDescription><upcs><upc type="UPC">00310119035863</upc></upcs><categories><category type="GS1" id="10000526">Eye Preparations</category></categories><created id="itemMaster">2013-10-23T00:00:00.000-05:00</created><lastUpdated id="itemMaster">2013-10-31T00:00:00.000-05:00</lastUpdated><media/><packageData type="Item" approximation="false"><length><measure>2.38</measure><uom>IN</uom></length><height><measure>6.65</measure><uom>IN</uom></height><width><measure>2.56</measure><uom>IN</uom></width><unitsInPackage>1</unitsInPackage><packageType id="bedf0a61-08f0-11de-abfb-1e0ad616ea54">BOX</packageType><packageSize><measure>10.0</measure><uom>OZ</uom></packageSize></packageData><products><product sequence="1" id="ffa40a50-3bef-11e3-8b51-005056ab0051" type="grocery"><description>Bausch + Lomb Biotrue Multi-Purpose Contact Solution</description><brand id="f805dad1-a9ba-11e1-89e7-005056ab0051">Bausch + Lomb</brand><manufacturer id="bbfabde0-9ae0-11e2-8d85-005056ab0051">Bausch + Lomb</manufacturer><countryOfOrigin>USA</countryOfOrigin><warnings><warning>Failure to discard solution from lens case after each use or use of water to care for your lenses may lead to contamination resulting in eye injury and potential loss of vision. See accompanying instructions for additional important safety information.
Do not use a heat disinfection regimen.
If you are allergic to any ingredient in this product, do not use.
Precautions:
Always discard solution from lens case after each use.
Keep the bottle tightly closed when not in use.
Store solution at room temperature.
Use before expiration date printed on the carton and bottle.
Discard any remaining solution 90 days after opening.
Keep out of reach of children.
Problems with contact lenses and lens care products could result in corneal infection and/or ulcer and lead to loss of vision. It is essential that you follow your eye care practitioner's directions and all labeling instructions for proper use of lenses and lens care products, including the lens case.
Eye problems, including corneal ulcers, can develop rapidly and lead to loss of vision. Daily wear lenses are not indicated for overnight wear and should not be worn while sleeping. Clinical studies have shown the risk of serious adverse reactions is increased when these lenses are worn overnight. Extended wear lenses should be regularly removed for cleaning and disinfection or for disposal and replacement on the schedule prescribed by your eye care professional. Clinical studies have shown that there is an increased incidence of serious adverse reactions in extended wear contact lens users as compared to daily wear contact lens users. Studies have also shown that the risk of serious adverse reactions increases the longer extended wear lenses are worn before removal for cleaning and disinfection or for disposal and replacement. Studies have also shown that smokers have a higher incidence of adverse reactions. If you experience eye discomfort, excessive tearing, vision changes, redness of the eye, immediately remove your lenses and promptly contact your eye care professional. It is recommended that contact lens wearers see their eye care professional twice each year, or if directed, more frequently.
You should follow the complete recommended lens rubbing and rinsing times in the product labeling to adequately disinfect your lenses and reduce the risk of contact lens contamination. Reduced rubbing or rinsing time may not adequately clean your lenses.
You should fill your lens case with fresh solution every time you store your lenses, and never "top-off" or re-use solution. You should discard your solution immediately after your lenses have been removed from the lens case. You should not expose or store your lenses in or rinse your lens case with any water, such as tap, bottled or distilled, or with any non-sterile solution.
Clean, rinse and air-dry your lens case each time you remove your lenses. In order to permit excess solution to drain, you can flip over your lens case while air drying. Replace your lens case frequently, depending upon your hygiene habits.
Failure to discard solution from lens case after each use or use of water to care for your lenses may lead to contamination resulting in eye injury and potential loss of vision. See accompanying instructions for additional important safety information.
Important safety information:
Always follow the product directions for use. Failure to follow product directions may lead to vision loss.
Visit your eye care practitioner regularly.
Always wash and dry hands before handling lenses.
Do not use tap water, bottled water or saliva with lenses or lens case.
Only use fresh solution to clean and disinfect contact lenses.
Always discard any remaining solution in your lens case after each disinfection cycle.
Saline or rewetting drops will not disinfect your lenses.
Always replace your solutions, lenses and lens case as directed.
To avoid contamination, do not touch tip of container to any surface. Replace cap after using.
Do not use with heat (thermal) disinfection.
Precautions:
Always discard solution from lens case after each use.
Keep the bottle tightly closed when not in use.
Store solution at room temperature.
Use before the expiration date marked on the carton and bottle.
Discard any remaining solution 90 days after opening.
Keep out of reach of children.
Adverse reactions (problems and what to do): the following problems may occur: eyes sting, burn or itch (irritation), comfort is less than when lens was first placed on the eye, feeling of something in the eye (foreign body, scratched area), excessive watering (tearing) of the eye, unusual eye secretions, redness of the eye, reduced sharpness of vision (poor visual acuity), blurred vision, rainbows or halos around objects, sensitivity to light (photophobia), or dry eyes.
If you notice any of the above:
Immediately remove your lenses.
If the discomfort or problem stops, then look closely at the lens.
If the lens is in any way damaged, do not put the lens back on your eye. Place the lens in the storage case and contact your eye care practitioner.
If the lens has dirt, an eyelash, or other foreign body on it, or the problem stops and the lens appears undamaged, thoroughly clean, rinse and disinfect the lens, then reinsert it.
If the problem continues, immediately remove the lens and consult your eye care practitioner.
If any of the above symptoms occur, a serious condition such as infection, corneal ulcer, neovascularization or iritis may be present. Seek immediate professional identification of the problem and prompt treatment to avoid serious eye damage.
Do not use if imprinted neckband on the bottle is broken or missing.</warning></warnings><directions>Free lens case included.
See inside of carton for directions for use and important safety information.
Storage: you may store your lenses up to a maximum of 30 days in the unopened lens case. If stored longer than 30 days between wear, you need to follow the cleaning and disinfecting steps prior to lens insertion.
Please read carefully and keep this package insert for future reference.
Conditions, cleans, removes protein, disinfects, rinses and stores.
To condition, clean, remove protein and disinfect lenses, complete these simple steps. This daily regimen is recommended by Bausch + Lomb for a healthy and comfortable contact lens wearing experience:
Step 1: Place at least 3 drops of Biotrue multi-purpose solution on each side of lens surface and gently rub for 20 seconds.
Step 2: Thoroughly rinse each side of the lens for 5 seconds with Biotrue multi-purpose solution.
Step 3: Place cleaned contact lenses in the lens case and fill with fresh Biotrue multi-purpose solution. Soak at least 4 hours. Remember to always use fresh solution - discard solution from lens case after each use.
Your lenses are now ready to wear. If any debris remains on contact lenses, rinse with Biotrue multi-purpose solution prior to insertion.
Always follow your eye care professional's instructions. Based upon your individual tear chemistry and lens-wearing schedule, your eye care professional may recommend additional products or procedures.
If not wearing contact lenses immediately, store them in a closed lens case. Do not store your lenses in simple saline in place of Biotrue multi-purpose solution. Saline solution will not disinfect.
Lenses may be stored in the unopened case until ready to wear, up to a maximum of 30 days. If you store your lenses for longer periods of time, they must be cleaned and disinfected with fresh Biotrue multi-purpose solution prior to lens insertion.
Actions: when used daily, Biotrue multi-purpose solution dissolves protein and cleans, loosens and removes accumulations of film, debris and deposits from soft contact lenses. Biotrue multi-purpose solution helps prevent the formation of irritating deposits on the lens surface. It kills harmful microorganisms on the lens. 
While your lens is soaking, the formula envelops the lens in a moisture-rich cushion to help the lens remain comfortable throughout the day. Biotrue multi-purpose solution can also be used to rinse lenses.
Biotrue benefits: Biotrue multi-purpose solution works like your eyes. It incorporates a lubricant also found in your eyes, and is balanced to match the pH of healthy tears. Biotrue multi-purpose solution cushions and rehydrates lenses for comfortable wear. Biotrue multi-purpose solution helps prevent certain tear proteins from denaturing for clean lenses and inhibits the formation of deposits that can cause discomfort and can shorten lens wearing time. By keeping lenses hydrated and clean, Biotrue multi-purpose solution makes wearing contact lenses comfortable all day. Biotrue. A solution that works like your eyes.
Indications (uses): Biotrue multi-purpose solution is indicated for use in the daily conditioning, cleaning, removal of protein deposits, rinsing, chemical (not heat) disinfection, and storage of soft (hydrophilic) contact lenses, including silicone hydrogel contact lenses, as recommended by your eye care practitioner. Contraindications (reasons not to use): if you are allergic to any ingredient in this product, do not use.
Good lens care hygiene:
Always wash and rinse your hands before you handle your lenses.
Clean, rinse and disinfect your lenses each time you remove them.
Always handle the same lens, the right or the left, first in order to avoid mixups.
After use, always empty and rinse the lens case with fresh Biotrue multi-purpose solution, and allow to air dry.</directions><grocery><foodRelatedIndicators/></grocery></product></products><attributes/></item><item id="017a5af0-6e15-11e1-b895-005056ab0051" status="P"><name>Arm &amp; Hammer Advance White Brilliant Sparkle Fluoride Anti-Cavity Gel Toothpaste</name><marketingDescription>Arm &amp; Hammer&#157;&#157;® Advance White®&#157;&#157; Brilliant Sparkle&#157;&#157; Fluoride Anti-Cavity Gel Toothpaste.

Preparation instructions:
Microwave oven*: (recommended).
1. Remove sandwich from wrapper. Place on microwaveable plate and cover with paper towel.
2. Microwave on high for 1 minute. Flip sandwich over and cook an additional 20-40 seconds or until hot.

Conventional oven*:

3. Bake for 15 minutes or until hot.
4. Carefully remove from oven and let stand 1 minute before serving.

Rockin' &amp; Roastin's artisanal roasts are of the highest quality Arabica coffee beans cultivated using organic, environmentally sustainable methods. Rockin'&amp; Roastin' chose the high-altitude, shade-loving Arabica beans, because they mature more slowly allowing them to develop a more intense and sensuous flavor, far surpassing that of its sun-loving coffee cousins grown at lower altitudes where rainforests have been decimated to make way for coffee crops. We use beans from the best coffee producing regions in the world - including Ethiopia, Indonesian Sumatra, and Guatemala, where certified organic farmers carefully monitor the crop, picking the glowing red coffee cherries at the zenith of ripeness.

Holiday Cookie Baking Instructions:
1. Store cookies in freezer until ready to use.
2. Heat oven to 375 degrees F.
3. Remove desired amount of cookies from freezer to bake.
4. Place cookies 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
5. Cookies may be baked frozen or, if desired, thaw for 10-15 minutes. 
6. Bake at 375 degrees F, until edges are light golden brown (10-12 minutes).*
7. Remove from oven.
8. Cool cookies on pan 5-10 minutes.
9. Remove cookies from pan with spatula and cool.

©The Jel Sert Company.</otherDescription><upcs><upc type="UPC">00072392330041</upc></upcs><categories><category type="GS1" id="10000312">Desserts (Shelf Stable)</category></categories><created id="itemMaster">2012-11-29T00:00:00.000-06:00</created><lastUpdated id="itemMaster">2012-12-12T00:00:00.000-06:00</lastUpdated><media/><packageData type="Item" approximation="true"><length><measure>1.32</measure><uom>IN</uom></length><height><measure>2.85</measure><uom>IN</uom></height><width><measure>3.48</measure><uom>IN</uom></width><unitsInPackage>1</unitsInPackage><packageType id="bedf0a61-08f0-11de-abfb-1e0ad616ea54">BOX</packageType><packageSize><measure>3.13</measure><uom>OZ</uom></packageSize><netWeight><measure>3.13</measure><uom>OZ</uom></netWeight></packageData><products><product sequence="1" id="fdd62440-3a3a-11e2-92cf-005056ab0051" type="grocery"><description>My-T-Fine Pudding &amp; Pie Filling Chocolate</description><brand id="45baf251-3a3a-11e2-92cf-005056ab0051">My-T-Fine</brand><manufacturer id="ff7719e1-cf59-11e1-9720-005056ab0051">The Jel Sert Company</manufacturer><directions>Pie directions:
1. Add 3 3/4 cups milk* to 2 (4-serving size) packages pudding mix in saucepan. (For 1 package pie, use 2 cups milk*). Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a full bubbling boil. Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
2. Pour into 9-inch baked pastry or crumb crust (use 8-inch crust for 1 package pie).
3. Refrigerate at least 4 hours or until set (3 hours for 1 package pie).
Pudding directions: 
1. Add 2 cups cold milk* to pudding mix in saucepan, stirring to keep mixture smooth.
2. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a full bubbling boil. Remove from heat. Pudding will thicken as it cools.
3. Pour into dishes. Cool slightly, then refrigerate at least 1/2 hour. For firmer set, refrigerate for 1 hour. Serve warm or cold. Makes 4 (1/2-cup) servings.
For creamier pudding, place plastic wrap directly on pudding surface before refrigerating. Stir pudding before serving.
*1% lowfat, skim, nonfat dry or lactose-reduced milk will cause soft set. Non-dairy creamer is not recommended.
Microwave directions:
1. Add 2 cups milk* to pudding mix in 1 1/2-quart microwavable bowl.
2. Cook on high Power 3 minutes. Stir. Cook 2 to 4 minutes** more or until mixture comes to a full bubbling boil, stirring every minute.
3. Stir well, pour into dishes and refrigerate at least 1/2 hour. For firmer set, refrigerate for 1 hour.
**Low wattage microwave ovens may require more time.</directions><grocery><ingredients>Sugar, Cornstarch, Cocoa (processed with Alkali), Food Starch Modified, contains less than 2% of the following: Cooking instructions:
Saute:
Preheat skillet on medium high for 1 minute.
Arrange frozen shrimp in a single layer in skillet.
Saute for 7 to 8 minutes or until shrimp turn orange outside and become white opaque inside.
Bake:
Preheat oven to 450 degrees F.
Arrange frozen shrimp in single layer in an oven safe dish.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes or until shrimp turn orange outside and become opaque white inside.
Microwave:
Place 1/2 package frozen shrimp in microwave safe bowl.
Cover with a paper towel.
Microwave on high for 3 to 3 1/2 minutes.
Shrimp are done when they turn orange outside and become opaque white inside*.
*Caution: bowl and scampi will be very hot. Microwave instructions were developed using an 1100 watt microwave oven.
